{
  "texts": [
    "Research DesignThis study follows a pretest-posttest experimental design with a control group, which allowed for the measurement of students' investigative skills before and after the intervention in both groups to compare the effects of the intervention (use of ChatGPT) on investigative competencies, ensuring a precise assessment of the tool's impact compared to traditional methods.The sample consisted of 100 regular basic education students, randomly assigned to two groups: an experimental group (n = 50) that used ChatGPT and a control group (n = 50) that employed traditional methods.",
    "Randomization ensured that both groups started with similar skill levels.",
    "Additionally, a pretest was administered to assess the students' initial investigative competencies, ensuring that any observed differences in the final skills would be exclusively due to the intervention.",
    "Statement of Objectives and Research Question 1) General questionTo what extent does the use of ChatGPT impact the development of investigative competencies in regular basic education students?2) Specific questions  What are the scores between the experimental and control groups?",
    " How do the scores vary between the experimental and control groups?"
  ]
}